Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
movePowerSwitch(25.10)                                  movePowerSwitch(25.10)

Name
       movePowerSwitch - The command is used to move power switch instances by
       offset value in X or Y direction

Syntax
       movePowerSwitch

       [-help]

       [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}]

       [-columnx <string>]

       [-fixOverlap]

        [-honorSoftBlockage]

       [-powerDomain <string>]

        [-reportFile <string>]

       [-selected]

        [-switchInstances <string>]

       [-xOffset <float>]

        [-yOffset <float>]

       The command is used to move power switch instances by offset value in X
       or  Y  direction. You can specify multiple power switch instances to be
       moved in the same offset value.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each movePowerSwitch parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man movePowerSwitch

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies moving the switches inside the indicated area.

       -columnx <string>
              Specifies moving columns at the indicated x locations.

       -fixOverlap
              Internally checks any overlap and fixes it  with  the  suggested
              offset value.

       -honorSoftBlockage
              When  used,  prevents  the  movePowerSwitch  command from moving
              power switch cells in areas having soft placement blockage.

       -powerDomain <string>
              Specifies moving the switches found in the indicated  power  do-
              main.

       -reportFile <string>
              Specifies  the  name  of the report file that stores information
              about the moved switches.

       -selected
              Specifies moving the selected switches.

       -switchInstances <string>
              Specifies moving the switches in the list.

       -xOffset <float>
              Specifies moving switches by the indicated amount in the  x  di-
              rection.

       -yOffset <float>
              Specifies  moving  switches by the indicated amount in the y di-
              rection.

Related Information
